{{Infobox artist | name = Georges Rochegrosse | image = Autoportrait Rochegrosse 1908.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Georges Rochegrosse. ''Self-portrait,'' 1908 | native_name = | native_name_lang = | birth_name = Georges-Antoine-Marie Rochegrosse | birth_date = 2 August 1859 | birth_place = Versailles, France | death_date = 11 July 1938 | death_place = Paris | resting_place = [[Montparnasse Cemetery]] | nationality = French | residence = France; Algeria | education = [[Jules Joseph Lefebvre]] and [[Gustave Boulanger]] in Paris | alma_mater = | known_for = Painter, illustrator, poster artist and etcher | notable_works = | style = | movement = [[Orientalism|Orientalist]] | spouse = Marie Leblond | partner = | awards = [[Legion of Honour|Officer of the Legion of Honor]](1892) | elected = | patrons = | memorials = | website = | module = }}
'''Georges Antoine Rochegrosse''' ({{IPA-fr|ʒɔʁʒ ɑ̃twan ʁɔʃɡʁɔs|lang}}; 1859&ndash;1938) was a French [[history painting|historical]] and decorative painter.
==Life and career== [[File:Marie Rochegrosse dans la Salle à Manger by Georges Rochegrosse.jpg|thumb|left|Marie Rochegrosse dans la Salle à Manger. Dated 1904]] [[File:Le Chevalier aux Fleurs 2560x1600.png|thumb|300px|''Le Chevalier aux Fleurs (The Knight of Flowers)'']] [[File:Georges Rochegrosse's poster for Jules Massenet's Don Quichotte.jpg|thumb|left|1910 poster for [[Jules Massenet]]'s ''[[Don Quichotte]]'']] He was born at [[Versailles (city)|Versailles]] and studied in [[Paris]] with [[Jules Joseph Lefebvre]] and [[Gustave Boulanger|Gustave Clarence Rodolphe Boulanger]]. <ref>Waller, S. (ed.), ''Foreign Artists and Communities in Modern Paris, 1870&ndash;1914: Strangers in Paradise,'' Routledge, 2017, p. 119.</ref> His themes are generally historical, and he treated them on a colossal scale and in an emotional naturalistic style, with a distinct revelling in horrible subjects and details. He made his [[Salon (Paris)|Paris Salon]] début in 1882 with ''Vitellis traîné dans les rues de Rome par la populace (Vitellius dragged through the streets of Rome by the people)'' (1882; Sens). He followed this the year afterwards with ''Andromaque'' (1882–83; [[Musée des Beaux-Arts de Rouen]]), which won that year's prestigious Prix du Salon. There followed ''La Jacquerie'' (1885; Untraced), ''Le mort de Babylone (The fall of Babylon)'' (1891; Untraced), ''The death of the Emperor Geta'' (1899; [[Musée de Picardie|Musée de Picardie, Amiens]]), and ''Barbarian ambassadors at the Court of Justinian'' (1907; Untraced), all of which exemplify his strong and spirited but sensational and often brutal painting. In quite another style and beautiful in color is his ''[[:File:Le Chevalier aux Fleurs 2560x1600.png|Le Chevalier aux Fleurs (The Knight of Flowers)]]'' (1894; [[Musée d'Orsay|Musée d’Orsay, Paris]]; RF 898).
He was elected an [[Legion of Honour|Officer of the Legion of Honor]] in 1892 and received the medal of honor in 1906 for ''The Red Delight''. Rochegrosse also illustrated several books. Some of the drawings for these illustrations are in the Department of Prints and Drawings at the British Museum, London. He lived his final years in Algeria, but returned to Paris where he died and is buried in [[Montparnasse Cemetery]]. His wife, Marie Rochegrosse (née Leblond), had died in 1920.
